      "kwargs": {
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "{\"success\":true,\"process_rule_id\":\"J09C\",\"process_rule\":\"1. Make a copy of decision_table with TOURS starting with J09C named J09C_temp.\\n2. Update the table with an additional empty column ENTSCHEIDUNG.\\n3. Apply the following rules to the joined table:\\n    1. Count the number of EQUNR for every HAUS and set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \\\"KSA\\\" if there are less than 3 EQUNR. ELSE set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \\\"EVU\\\".\\n    2. Set all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 of 0 to \\\"EVU\\\".\\n    3. Set all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 from 500 to 599 to \\\"EVU\\\".\\n4. Join this table with the EABLG table using INSTALLATION.\\n5. Join this table with the NET_MASTER table and the SALES_MASTER table using EQUNR.\\n6. Compare sales data and net data for these IDs:\\n    - If sales data is there, take sales data and empty net data.\\n    - Otherwise stay with net data and empty sales data.\\n7. Export the final data from the table as CSV file named J09C including the columns: `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`.\\n8. Send them to the EVU team to meter.readings@evu.com.\\n9. Delete the temporary table after exporting the data.\"}",
            "id": "lc_08e20f31-7882-4429-902b-e611debae3f6"
          }
        ],
        "type": "tool",
        "name": "retrieve_process",
        "id": "d1eba8be-497a-48c3-b351-326c1a480d07",
        "tool_call_id": "call_mld8VtDWUARTR2XGJVm1pn6Y",
        "artifact": {
          "structured_content": {
            "success": true,
            "process_rule_id": "J09C",
            "process_rule": "1. Make a copy of decision_table with TOURS starting with J09C named J09C_temp.\n2. Update the table with an additional empty column ENTSCHEIDUNG.\n3. Apply the following rules to the joined table:\n    1. Count the number of EQUNR for every HAUS and set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \"KSA\" if there are less than 3 EQUNR. ELSE set ENTSCHEIDUNG to \"EVU\".\n    2. Set all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 of 0 to \"EVU\".\n    3. Set all houses with HOUSE_NUM1 from 500 to 599 to \"EVU\".\n4. Join this table with the EABLG table using INSTALLATION.\n5. Join this table with the NET_MASTER table and the SALES_MASTER table using EQUNR.\n6. Compare sales data and net data for these IDs:\n    - If sales data is there, take sales data and empty net data.\n    - Otherwise stay with net data and empty sales data.\n7. Export the final data from the table as CSV file named J09C including the columns: `Meter Reading (MR) Doc. No.`, `HAUS`, `ANLAGE`, `ME_MA_ID`, `EQUNR`, `HOUSE_NUM1`, `ENTSCHEIDUNG`, `TITLE`, `FORENAME`, `SURNAME`, `STREET`, `STREETNO`, `POST_CODE1`, `CITY1`, `CITY2`, `EMAIL`.\n8. Send them to the EVU team to meter.readings@evu.com.\n9. Delete the temporary table after exporting the data."
          }
        },
        "status": "success"
      }
    },
